Have you ever had shower problems before? That’ll tell me how to explain it
depends on the problem I guess

So we have a single handle faucet. So it’s not a knob. You have to pull it out and then turn it to let hot or cold water in. A cartridge connects your handle to the hot and cold pipes.  So Ciera and I broke the faucet and half the screw in the cartridge. So you could turn the cartridge by hand but the handle was off. I’ve replaced cartridges before you just have to take off the face plate the clamp and then just yank that shit. But this one was stuck. So I literally had every semi handyman in my family come over at some point over the last month to help me with it. My dad suggested just sawing it off and basically cutting a fake pipe and cartridge to replace it. 

Eventually I called a plumber and me and him like drowned the think in CLR and Wd40 and anything to loosen it up. But it didn’t work.

So the guy let’s me know that the pipes connecting the top (shower) and bottom (faucet) are galvanized. So the only way I can get it out is to at least try to burn it out. With like a blowtorch and hope for the best. Now the issue with that is that if you’re setting your pipes on fire they’re not going work anymore. So if burning doesn’t work then you have to replace every pipe. Which means breaking down a wall. So you could break down the bathroom wall which essentially just gives Ciera the green light for a 5000 buck bathroom renovation or you go into the bedroom and knock out that wall where all id have to do is get the plywood and stuff and sand it up to replace the wall which is maybe a couple 100. So I had him come back this morning with his blowtorch and he just blasted the shit and yanked out the cartridge and a bunch of other shit he’d never seen before. So now he’s out looking for an antique plumber specialist (???) to see what can replace it. But it looks like I may not have to knock down a wall.
